,Recommended,314560,18992069,"Posted: 10 November, 2015",all,ArtesQ,"What attracted me about this game is that the screenshots looked really good. Without even consulting the ""About"" I made the decision to buy this game.At first glance the game seems well designed with nice art and fairly descent sized maps. Starting the game and getting used to the controls needs some practice. So be certain to look through all the controls before you starting playing.You start of with two characters which both can control together or seperatly, which is tottaly new to me. Atleast in this kind of game. So this can be of a struggle from time to time.Environment:What i've encountered so far the world looks good and well designed but if you look more closely you find some minor flaws ( yes i'm getting very nitpicky here), the ground clutter could use some more variation, at some places in the world you will find areas where the ground clutter is practilly the same all over. At some times this seems very unnatural.Second, the finishing of some objects for instance, rock staircases, instead of putting edges on them they covered it with rocks and boulders which is a shame, cause the textures of the game seem really good, I rather would've seen some more time spend into designing such stuff.Further more it seems pretty well designed and even though they've used low poly trees, they made it work really well. And if you don't look the the enviroment to well you wont even notice the points noted above.Gameplay:You start of with two character you can both control at the same time or individually. Which may need some practice but  you'll get the hang of it after a while. You control what to make of your characters, either make them a healer, archer or warrior. In the begging you can choose between 9 spells ( 3 for healer, 3 for archer and 3 for warrior). You can pick what kind of spells your character can use. With leveling up you can also choose how to strengthen you character, do you want your character to have more health and attack, choose body, and etc. Points awarded for each skill like body can be reassigned again if you want to, for example, your character to be an archer. You hold the power to do so.  While traveling through the land of Kyn, you will find many enemies to 'hack and slash'. Colors above their body suggests how strong they are. For example grey = weak, red is bit stronger and so on. Whilst roaming you will find UPC who will need help. Here you find your quests, this ofcourse can be various takst to complete. For finishing quest you will be awared loot or gold. Also, before I forget to mention it, mobs will also drop loot. The stronger the mob, the better the loot.Throughout playing the game you will find puzzles you will have to complete with the help of both characters. Sometimes you have to control your characters seperatly to finish this puzzle and get further into the storyline of the game. Puzzles are well designed and thought. It may need some practice and brain cramps but you'll get there eventually. Some puzzles are ofcourse harder then other, but still understandable for everyone.Loot:I probably won't have to tell you this. But i'm still going to do so. Loot can come in many form and shapes. Loot can be gold, crafting items, armor and weapons. Weapons and Armour will get better the further you will get into the game. The game uses colour codes for the item. Grey items being the 'weakest' for instance purple are 'stronger' and get extra bonuses such as, +8 damage. This is the same for crafting items, the further you get in the game, the better the items become. And ofcourse you can craft better items with those.Crafting:Havent tried it yet -- so further information will be here soon.But still the basics, the better crafting items you have, the stronger of items you can craft.Controls:In my opinion this could've been designed better. Although you can costumise your own control to make it work a little bit better. With 'A', 'W' and 'E' you control the basic spells of each character. You can switch between them by using the 1 and 2 keys. Haggling between them to keep both character is a little getting used to in the beginning, but you'll get used to it. Or just use 'Tab' to switch between characters. The struggle sometimes is, espescially during a larger fight knowing when you're in control of both characters or not. It's best to know before hand how to properly control both character else you will make it harder for yourself. Where in most games this is second nature, it isnt here.Moving your characters is doing by clicking the right mouse button, instead of holding it and let the characters move to the point of where your mouse is,  you have to click again and again to get your characters where you want. But this can be a personal preference. Up to you to decide which is nicer.Movement of character, whether your character of 10 pixels appart of 100 pixels appart. Whern you move both characters at the same time, the distance between them will be kept the same. Which unintentially can cause, that the character you dont want to be in front, will be in the front of the fight. So switching between characters all the time can be a bit frustrating. But maybe is just because im tottaly not used to it, it is new for me.To add to the part of clicking and hold to move, when youre in town apperently this function excist by using your left mouse button, but when youre out in the field. The function doesn't seem to excist. Bit weird?, but oke.In conclusion, the game seems really well made and thought of , world can be designed a little bit better ( but this not of a big deal at all). The fighting against mobs seems good, occassionally your character can get stuck between them. But as long you can control your characters well it doesnt seem to be a haggle. The game could need some little bit of polishing but the base seems really firm. Defently worth a try.PS.Forgot about talking about the ""Slow Time"" button which can be used in fight to help you assist in placing your characters in the fight. Which can come in very usefull if your character are in low health and you need some quick healing to be done."
